<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="160" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1313,1556]" pageId="3" pageNumber="160">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,1313,1340]" pageId="3" pageNumber="160">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Elongate and thin bug (total length varying between 7 and 
<quantity box="[949,1017,1314,1340]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="160" unit="mm" value="8.0">8 mm</quantity>
, total width about 
<quantity box="[1229,1299,1314,1340]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="160" unit="mm" value="1.0">1 mm</quantity>
). Pilosity of two first antennal segments, femora and tibia erect, elongate, obviously longer than the corresponding segment. Fourth antennal segment shorter than the second (Carvalho 1992). Apex of labium reaching metacoxae. Cuneus obviously longer than wide at base. Ostiolar peritreme yellowish. Left paramere with long setae subapically on its dorso-outer margin. Body of right paramere narrow, its apex simple.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
